{"asset_id": "asset_a5252f916718d3fdd7757380", "problem_id": "prob_c11f4ea0de15f097c71f67f5", "asset_type": "text", "asset_role": "question_text_normalized", "source_uri": null, "storage_uri": "inline://prob_c11f4ea0de15f097c71f67f5/question_normalized", "file_format": "txt", "file_size_bytes": 322, "width": null, "height": null, "sha256": "156782c916e49442bed26b943821b7fa2f99cdca13ce558cee45cd016b7b6557", "perceptual_hash": null, "source_text_snapshot": "As shown in the figure, in the known $\\triangle ABC$, proceed with the following steps: \n(1) With centers at B and C, respectively, draw arcs with radii longer than $\\frac{1}{2}BC$, intersecting at points M and N; \n(2) Draw line MN intersecting AB at D, and connect CD. If $AC = 5$ and $AB = 12$, what is the perimeter of $\\triangle ACD$?", "normalized_text_snapshot": "As shown in the figure, in $\\triangle ABC$, perform the following steps: (1) With centers at $B$ and $C$, draw arcs with radii greater than $\\frac{1}{2}BC$ that intersect at points $M$ and $N$. (2) Draw line $MN$, intersecting $AB$ at $D$, and connect $CD$. If $AC=5$ and $AB=12$, what is the perimeter of $\\triangle ACD$?", "text_completeness_score": 0.8, "blur_score": null, "readability_score": null, "noise_score": null, "cropped_from_asset_id": null, "roi_bbox": null, "unit_normalization_map": [], "variable_aliases": [{"original": "As", "canonical": "As", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "in", "canonical": "in", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "the", "canonical": "the", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "ABC", "canonical": "ABC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "With", "canonical": "With", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "at", "canonical": "at", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "B", "canonical": "B", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "and", "canonical": "and", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "C", "canonical": "C", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "draw", "canonical": "draw", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "arcs", "canonical": "arcs", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "with", "canonical": "with", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "than", "canonical": "than", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "frac", "canonical": "frac", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "BC", "canonical": "BC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "that", "canonical": "that", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "M", "canonical": "M", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "N", "canonical": "N", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "Draw", "canonical": "Draw", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "line", "canonical": "line", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "MN", "canonical": "MN", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "AB", "canonical": "AB", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "D", "canonical": "D", "variable_type": "symbol"}, {"original": "CD", "canonical": "CD", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "If", "canonical": "If", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "AC", "canonical": "AC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "is", "canonical": "is", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "of", "canonical": "of", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "ACD", "canonical": "ACD", "variable_type": "label"}], "asset_quality_flags": [], "is_usable": true, "discard_reason_codes": [], "created_at": "2026-04-03T17:12:09Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-03T17:12:09Z"}
{"asset_id": "asset_692cc6334528b191a887c1db", "problem_id": "prob_c11f4ea0de15f097c71f67f5", "asset_type": "answer", "asset_role": "answer_raw", "source_uri": "source://mm_math/train/52950677.png/answer", "storage_uri": "inline://prob_c11f4ea0de15f097c71f67f5/answer_raw", "file_format": "txt", "file_size_bytes": 210, "width": null, "height": null, "sha256": "c912950757738a06808327e8e29d22bf84e1f1b507a199a55b12f8dc1bc704a3", "perceptual_hash": null, "source_text_snapshot": "\\textbf{Solution:} From the construction, we have that $MN$ bisects $BC$ perpendicularly,\\\\\n$\\therefore DB=DC$,\\\\\n$\\therefore$ the perimeter of $\\triangle ACD = AC+AD+CD = AC+AD+BD = AC+AB = 5+12 = \\boxed{17}$.", "normalized_text_snapshot": null, "text_completeness_score": 1.0, "blur_score": null, "readability_score": null, "noise_score": null, "cropped_from_asset_id": null, "roi_bbox": null, "unit_normalization_map": [], "variable_aliases": [{"original": "From", "canonical": "From", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "the", "canonical": "the", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "MN", "canonical": "MN", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "is", "canonical": "is", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "of", "canonical": "of", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "BC", "canonical": "BC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "so", "canonical": "so", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "DB", "canonical": "DB", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "DC", "canonical": "DC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "ACD", "canonical": "ACD", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "AC", "canonical": "AC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "AD", "canonical": "AD", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "CD", "canonical": "CD", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "BD", "canonical": "BD", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "AB", "canonical": "AB", "variable_type": "label"}], "asset_quality_flags": [], "is_usable": true, "discard_reason_codes": [], "created_at": "2026-04-03T17:12:09Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-03T17:12:09Z"}
{"asset_id": "asset_2fdcaa7b34672bb86849250b", "problem_id": "prob_c11f4ea0de15f097c71f67f5", "asset_type": "answer", "asset_role": "answer_normalized", "source_uri": null, "storage_uri": "inline://prob_c11f4ea0de15f097c71f67f5/answer_normalized", "file_format": "txt", "file_size_bytes": 168, "width": null, "height": null, "sha256": "0cf329e13415013f04c2e50bcb9e49b3f67f1feb1fd498b548ae0b89a5733659", "perceptual_hash": null, "source_text_snapshot": "\\textbf{Solution:} From the construction, we have that $MN$ bisects $BC$ perpendicularly,\\\\\n$\\therefore DB=DC$,\\\\\n$\\therefore$ the perimeter of $\\triangle ACD = AC+AD+CD = AC+AD+BD = AC+AB = 5+12 = \\boxed{17}$.", "normalized_text_snapshot": "From the construction, $MN$ is the perpendicular bisector of $BC$, so $DB=DC$. Therefore, the perimeter of $\\triangle ACD$ is $AC+AD+CD=AC+AD+BD=AC+AB=5+12=\\boxed{17}$.", "text_completeness_score": 1.0, "blur_score": null, "readability_score": null, "noise_score": null, "cropped_from_asset_id": null, "roi_bbox": null, "unit_normalization_map": [], "variable_aliases": [{"original": "From", "canonical": "From", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "the", "canonical": "the", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "MN", "canonical": "MN", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "is", "canonical": "is", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "of", "canonical": "of", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "BC", "canonical": "BC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "so", "canonical": "so", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "DB", "canonical": "DB", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "DC", "canonical": "DC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "ACD", "canonical": "ACD", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "AC", "canonical": "AC", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "AD", "canonical": "AD", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "CD", "canonical": "CD", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "BD", "canonical": "BD", "variable_type": "label"}, {"original": "AB", "canonical": "AB", "variable_type": "label"}], "asset_quality_flags": [], "is_usable": true, "discard_reason_codes": [], "created_at": "2026-04-03T17:12:09Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-03T17:12:09Z"}
